text.section:
Subject to the authority of the Executive Director, the Victim Services Coordinator shall:
provide staff support to the Board on victim services matters;
monitor, assess, and make recommendations on State and local victim compensation programs and procedures;
provide technical assistance to local public and private programs that provide victim assistance;
research and gather data on victims and victim assistance programs, and disseminate the data to the public;
submit to the Governor, the Attorney General, the Secretary of Public Safety and Correctional Services, and the Board an annual report that includes recommendations on how to improve victim assistance programs;
ensure that the rights of victims are observed;
help victims to get the information to which they have a right; and
monitor compliance with the guidelines for treatment of and assistance to victims and witnesses under §§ 11-1002 and 11-1003 of this title.
